2026-04-21 02:40:32 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=[] hypothesis_explanation="The missing red indicator LEDs (switch indicators) in all control modules prevent current from flowing through the entire series path. In this circuit, each control module's indicator LED and its series resistor provide the only path for current flow through each module when its switch is ON. If the LEDs are removed (open circuit), no current can flow between the modules, and thus, the path to the load (lamp) is interrupted. This explains why neither the lamp nor the load indicator turns on, even when all switches are set to ON. The observed symptoms (all control LEDs missing, lamp doesn't turn on) are fully accounted for by the complete absence of all indicator LEDs in the control modules. The root cause is not a failed component, but the absence (removal) of essential circuit elements (the indicator LEDs)."
