2026-04-21 02:41:06 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Control Module 1', 'Control Module 2', 'Control Module 3', 'Control Module 4', 'Control Module 5', 'Control Module 6', 'Control Module 7', 'Control Module 8'] hypothesis_explanation='All control module indicator LEDs and their series resistors have been physically removed from each control module. This removal leaves an open circuit at each indicator LED point: since the LED-resistor path is in parallel with the switch but in series with the main circuit, its absence breaks continuity for the 12V/0V circuit through each module, interrupting current flow. This explains why neither the lamp nor the load indicator function. The main 12V path may visually appear intact, but the absence of the LED-resistor bridges creates a series open circuit. Restoring continuity in these positions would restore operation.'
